              "subtype": "activation_type",
              "type": "stat_block_section",
              "value": "interact"
            }
          ],
          "effect": "You pull the hood of the mantle over your face, revealing the six eyes of Grogrisant. The mantle gives off a flash of blinding light in a 60-foot emanation. All enemies within this area must attempt a DC 38 Fortitude saving throw. On a failure, they're blinded for 1 minute. On a critical failure, they're permanently blinded.",
          "frequency": "once per day",
          "links": [
            {
              "alt": "blinded",
              "aonid": 1,
              "game-obj": "Conditions",
              "name": "blinded",
              "type": "link"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Activate",
          "subtype": "activation",
          "traits": [
            {
              "edition": "legacy",
              "game-id": "01bf3e53d6c0fc7f70419341635bfe8f",
              "game-obj": "Traits",
              "name": "Evocation",
              "sources": [
                {
                  "errata": {
                    "alt": "4.0",
                    "aonid": 1,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "4.0",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "link": {
                    "alt": "Core Rulebook pg. 631",
                    "aonid": 1,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "Core Rulebook pg. 631",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "name": "Core Rulebook",
                  "page": 631,
                  "type": "source"
                }
              ],
              "text": "Effects and magic items with this trait are associated with the evocation school of magic, typically involving energy and elemental forces.",
              "type": "trait"
            },
            {
              "alternate_link": {
                "alternate_type": "legacy",
                "aonid": 93,
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "type": "alternate_link"
              },
              "edition": "remastered",
              "game-id": "b26076555c07646f046dd58e7d5b3885",
              "game-obj": "Traits",
              "name": "Incapacitation",
              "sources": [
                {
                  "errata": {
                    "alt": "2.0",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "2.0",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "link": {
                    "alt": "Player Core pg. 457",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "Player Core pg. 457",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "name": "Player Core",
                  "page": 457,
                  "type": "source"
                }
              ],
              "text": "An ability with this trait can take a character completely out of the fight or even kill them, and it\u2019s harder to use on a more powerful character. If a spell has the incapacitation trait, any creature of more than twice the spell\u2019s rank treats the result of their check to prevent being incapacitated by the spell as one degree of success better, or the result of any check the spellcaster made to incapacitate them as one degree of success worse. If any other effect has the incapacitation trait, a creature of higher level than the item, creature, or hazard generating the effect gains the same benefits.",
              "type": "trait"
            },
            {
              "alternate_link": {
                "alternate_type": "legacy",
                "aonid": 100,
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "type": "alternate_link"
              },
              "edition": "remastered",
              "game-id": "dd40587ebc07c2b386aa95d93fdcc130",
              "game-obj": "Traits",
              "name": "Light",
              "sources": [
                {
                  "errata": {
                    "alt": "2.0",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "2.0",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "link": {
                    "alt": "Player Core pg. 458",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "Player Core pg. 458",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "name": "Player Core",
                  "page": 458,
                  "type": "source"
                }
              ],
              "text": "Light effects overcome non-magical darkness in the area and can counteract magical darkness. You must usually target darkness magic with your light magic directly to counteract the darkness, but some light spells automatically attempt to counteract darkness.",
              "type": "trait"
            },
            {
              "alternate_link": {
                "alternate_type": "legacy",
                "aonid": 134,
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "type": "alternate_link"
              },
              "edition": "remastered",
              "game-id": "60a4f011afd1e0fac8211bd01108d104",
              "game-obj": "Traits",
              "name": "Primal",
              "sources": [
                {
                  "errata": {
                    "alt": "2.0",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "2.0",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "link": {
                    "alt": "Player Core pg. 460",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "Player Core pg. 460",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "name": "Player Core",
                  "page": 460,
                  "type": "source"
                }
              ],
              "text": "This magic comes from the primal tradition, connecting to the natural world and instinct. Anything with this trait is magical.  \n  \nA creature with this trait is primarily constituted of or has a strong connection to primal magic.",
              "type": "trait"
            },
            {
              "alternate_link": {
                "alternate_type": "legacy",
                "aonid": 163,
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "type": "alternate_link"
              },
              "edition": "remastered",
              "game-id": "abcdb0d656f37cebdbee9dca267ef899",
              "game-obj": "Traits",
              "name": "Visual",
              "sources": [
                {
                  "errata": {
                    "alt": "2.0",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "2.0",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "link": {
                    "alt": "Player Core pg. 463",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "Player Core pg. 463",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "name": "Player Core",
                  "page": 463,
                  "type": "source"
                }
              ],
              "text": "A visual effect can affect only creatures that can see it. This applies only to visible parts of the effect, as determined by the GM.",
              "type": "trait"
            }
          ],
          "type": "stat_block_section"
        }
      ],
      "subtype": "statistics",
      "type": "stat_block_section",
      "usage": {
        "subtype": "usage",
        "text": "worn cloak",
        "type": "stat_block_section"
